This paper deals with the reengineering of GSM/GPRS for smart metering, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues related to smart metering, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of GSM/GPRS for smart metering involves data transmission and processing, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes mechanisms for access control, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of smart metering on the environment, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
